## ARCHITECTURE REFACTOR REQUIRED? **NO**
- The existing feature-based architecture is fundamentally sound
- All fixes are additive or in-place corrections
- The BigInt→UUID migration is flagged but is a **database migration** of very high effort and risk, recommended for a separate phase

> [!WARNING]
> The UUID migration (FEAT-SERVER-04) would require: new Prisma migration, data migration for all 9 tables, updating all BigInt references throughout the codebase. This is a **separate initiative** and should NOT be bundled with these fixes.

## RISK ASSESSMENT

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| RPC type fix surfacing hidden type errors | High | Medium | Fix errors as they appear, all are currently masked by `any` |
| Homepage stats API adding latency to page load | Low | Low | Use React Query staleTime and show skeleton during load |
| Google Translate fix breaking in some browsers | Medium | Low | Test across Chrome, Firefox, Safari |
| OTP email blocked by DEP-01 | Certain | High | Document as known limitation, proceed when approved |

